// The inverse of matrix A (with entries s(i,j)*a^(i-j)) in lower matrix form:
//
// inverse(A) = 
//  [  1      0      0      0      ... ]
//  [ 1/a     1      0      0      ... ]
//  [1/a²    3/a     1      0      ... ]
//  [1/a³   7/a²    6/a     1      ... ]
//  [1/a⁴  15/a³   25/a²   10/a    1   ... ]
//  [ ...    ...    ...     ...    ... ... ]
//
// The (i,j) entry is S(i,j)*a^(j-i) where S(i,j) is the Stirling number of the second kind
